events.1294: Wednesdays and Saturdays designated market days
events.1417: Eric of Pomerania takes Copenhagen Castle
events.1661: Coat of arms of Copenhagen granted
events.1683: Palace built for Ulrik Frederik Gyldenløve
events.1742: Royal Danish Academy of Sciences and Letters established
events.1787: J. Cl. Todes Døtreskole, the first secondary school for girls, is founded
events.1793: Royal Danish Library opened to the public
events.1807: Royal Commission for the Preservation of Antiquities established
events.1815: Copenhagen Court House (with city hall) built at Nytorv
events.1825: Royal Danish Academy of Music founded
events.1865: Hansen Writing Ball typewriter invented in Copenhagen
events.1894: Frederik's Church, popularly known as the 'Marble Church', opens
events.1901: Museum of Copenhagen and International Secretariat of National Trade Union Centres founded
events.1905: Copenhagen City Hall built on City Hall Square
events.1911: Copenhagen Central Station, Idrætsparken, and Hirschsprung Collection open
events.1925: Copenhagen Airport, Kastrup and Bakkehuset museum open
events.1951: World's first successful sex reassignment surgery performed at Gentofte Hospital
events.1957: World Santa Claus Congress begins near city
events.2000: Øresund Bridge opens to Malmö, Sweden
events.2007: Fictional The Killing (TV series) begins broadcasting
events.2008: Royal Danish Playhouse opens in Frederiksstaden
events.2009: United Nations Climate Change Conference held
events.2015: 14–15 February: 2015 Copenhagen shootings occur, killing two civilians and wounding five police officers
